    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-09-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-09-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="1318"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1318">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 701.6311/152</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Austro-Hungarian Ambassador</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_DCT1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dumba</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Third Assistant Secretary of State</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_PW1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-09-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 8, 1915</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Phillips</hi>: As the papers begin to publish
                    spurious texts of my letter to <persName>Baron Burian</persName>, I should like
                    to be able to refer to the real one, or at least to its English translation
                    cabled to the State Department. Could you be kind enough to ask Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_LR1">Lansing</persName> to have a copy of it forwarded to me to
                    New York, St. Regis Hotel, still to-day, as I shall only return to Lenox on
                    Saturday from New York.</p>
                <p>These papers are a nightmare.</p>
                <p>Many thanks from yours very sincerely,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DCT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">C. Dumba</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
